{"TopicId":147120,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Shinies?","CreatedByName":"Sharpy","CreatedById":145504,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-05T14:00:19Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Sharpy","CreatedById":145504,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-05T14:00:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a mod that provides lights that don\u0027t cast light around, just shine in the darkness - a\u0027la the red lights on Poodle, or the LED indicator on a small battery?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m happily using this one:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/139724-112-surface-mounted-stock-alike-lights-for-self-illumination-v124-052316/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbut...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ENOTES\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nBy default KSP allows only 8 simultaneous lights in a single area. If some of your lights aren\u0027t showing correctly, raise the \u0022pixel light count\u0022 in the settings.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nEvery light in the scene adds rendering complexity. Avoid adding too many lights to not impact FPS.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0AFAIK these indicator lights on batteries and the likes don\u0027t cause that problem. Of course they provide no illumination around, but they are visible in darkness, which is all I\u0027m asking for.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there some mod providing this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pizzaoverhead","CreatedById":26349,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-05T14:12:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027re looking for lights that use emissives rather than a full light source. The closest thing to this is \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/74092-0242-glowstrips-v043/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EGlowStrips\u003C/a\u003E. It hasn\u0027t been updated lately, but still works.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sharpy","CreatedById":145504,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-05T14:29:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222742828\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147120\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221473084728\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002226349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022pizzaoverhead\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, pizzaoverhead said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027re looking for lights that use emissives rather than a full light source. The closest thing to this is \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/74092-0242-glowstrips-v043/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EGlowStrips\u003C/a\u003E. It hasn\u0027t been updated lately, but still works.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNice. I wonder if I can tweakscale them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sebi.zzr","CreatedById":81294,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-05T20:43:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/145504-sharpy/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022145504\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/145504-sharpy/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Sharpy\u003C/a\u003E,\u003C/span\u003Ethe aviation lights are not too bright except the strobe ones.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/137806-113-indicatorlights-v10-small-convenient-informative/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/16801-113-aviation-lights-v39-fixed-by-moardv/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sharpy","CreatedById":145504,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-06T02:25:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/81294-sebizzr/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002281294\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/81294-sebizzr/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sebi.zzr\u003C/a\u003E Aviation lights are still full lights, but Indicator lights do what I wanted... mostly \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E I mean, the surface-mounted one from the pack does.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpannerMonkey(smce)","CreatedById":50907,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-06T03:01:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222743672\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147120\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221473128741\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022145504\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022S